
1. in java there are have 2-types of lock
    a) Object Level Lock
    b) Class Level Lock

 2. Class Level Lock
        for every class one 'Class class object' created internally in JVM Architecture
        this topic is covered.

 3. If your thread want to execute a static synchronized method then thread required
    class level lock, once thread got class level lock then it is allowed to execute
    any static synchronized method of that class.
    Once method execute complete autometically thread releases lock